Description: Windows 11-like Wayland desktop environment for Linux
 LWinDesk is a lightweight Wayland desktop environment for Linux that
 provides a familiar Windows 11-like experience. It consists of a wlroots-based
 compositor with server-side decorations and a Qt6/QML shell providing the
 visual UI.
 .
 Features include:
  * Centered taskbar with system tray and clock
  * Start menu with application grid and search
  * Window snap layouts and zones
  * Virtual desktop switching
  * Notification center and quick settings panel
  * Server-side window decorations with title bars
  * Desktop wallpaper support
  * Keyboard shortcuts (Super key, Alt+Tab, etc.)
